  "definitions": [
    "(transitive, intransitive) to hear",
    "(uncommon) to attend, listen (to), pay attention (to)",
    "(by extension, uncommon) to understand"
  ],
  "description": "udire",
  "etymology": "From Latin audīre, present active infinitive of audiō, from Proto-Indo-European *h₂ew-is-d-, a compound of Proto-Indo-European *h₂ewis (“clearly, manifestly”) (from the root *h₂ew- (“to see, perceive”)) and *dʰh₁-ye/o- (“to render”).",
